Sewing will be slow with this project. Work your sewing machine by slowing turning the hand wheel by hand and giving just enough power to move over these sections very slowly. The upholstery thread is very thick, so to make things go faster, fill up several sewing machine bobbins with your upholstery thread, so you do not constantly have to un-thread and refill the same bobbin. Increased thickness of fabric, at corners or fold seams, requires that you wear your safety goggles while stitching. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/c/ce/I8c-sml.jpg/460px-I8c-sml.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/c/ce/I8c-sml.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":345,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":570.3564727954972,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/2.5/">Creative Commons</a><br>
